Do the needful

Let's understand - This is a common Indian way of closing a mail or an application. However, you will not find the usage of this expression beyond India. Thus, it can be thought of as an example of Indianism in the English language.

Incorrect Usage- I request you to do the needful.

Correct Usages- I request you to do what is required/ needed.
- I request you to suggest the next course of action.
- I request you to assist/ help me in this regard.
